ned to have very modest goals for society and myself  things like clean air  green grass  children with bright eyes  not being pushed around  useful work that suits one''s abilities  plain tasty food  and occasional satisfying nookie.', 11646, 0), (404272, 'If you would hit the mark  you must aim a little above it: Every arrow that flies feels the attraction of earth.', 147, 0), (404273, 'Ah  but a man''s reach should exceed his grasp  or what''s a heaven for?', 698, 0), (404274, 'Before we set our hearts too much upon anything  let us examine how happy they are  who already possess it.', 62191, 0), (404275, 'Ours is a world where people don''t know what they want and are willing to go through hell to get it.', 2692, 0), (404276, 'Accept the place the divine providence has found for you  the society of your contemporaries  the connection of events.', 760, 0), (404277, 'Those who aim at great deeds must also suffer greatly.', 4891, 0), (404278, 'It is a mistake to look too far ahead. Only one link in the chain of destiny can be handled at a time.', 3621, 0), (404279, 'Do not wish to be anything but what you are  and try to be that perfectly.', 27065, 0), (404280, 'This one thing I do  forgetting those things which are behind  and reaching forth unto those things which are before  I press toward the mark!', 5587, 0), (404281, 'Winning isn''t everything  but wanting to win is.', 5571, 0), (404282, 'It is no longer clear which way is up even if one wants to rise.', 28621, 0), (404283, 'Ambition is pitiless. Any merit that it cannot use it finds despicable.', 8895, 0), (404284, 'Every man is said to have his peculiar ambition.', 1012, 0), (404285, 'Well is it known that ambition can creep as well as soar.', 2026, 0), (404286, 'Make no little plans  they have no magic to stir men''s blood . . . Make big plans  aim high in hope and work.', 63970, 0), (404287, 'An aim in life is the only fortune worth finding.', 5637, 0), (404288, 'You have to have a dream so you can get up