760, 0), (404680, 'The best thing must be to flee from all to the All.', 2751, 0), (404681, 'A humble knowledge of oneself is a surer road to God than a deep searching of the sciences.', 946, 0), (404682, 'By learning to contact  listen to  and act on our intuition  we can directly connect to the higher power of the universe and allow it to become our guiding force.', 39554, 0), (404683, 'It''s only by forgetting yourself that you draw near to God.', 1049, 0), (404684, 'Some people talk about finding God  as if He could get lost.', 33, 0), (404685, 'Hunting God is a great adventure.', 64035, 0), (404686, 'In the faces of men and women I see God.', 1127, 0), (404687, 'To Be is to live with God.', 760, 0), (404688, 'Nothing hath separated us from God but our own will  or rather our own will is our separation from God.', 21439, 0), (404689, 'The kingdom of God is within you.', 5587, 0), (404690, 'Not only then has each man his individual relation to God  but each man has his peculiar relation to God.', 3992, 0), (404691, 'Because you cannot see him  God is everywhere.', 9537, 0), (404692, 'All who call on God in true faith  earnestly from the heart  will certainly be heard  and will receive what they have asked and desired.', 1746, 0), (404693, 'The light of God surrounds me  The love of God enfolds me  The power of God protects me  The Presence of God watches over me  Wherever I am  God is.', 64036, 0), (404694, 'To think you are separate from God is to remain separate from your own being.', 64037, 0), (404695, 'So great was my joy in God that I took no heed of looking at the angels and the saints  because all their goodness and all their beauty was from Him and in Him.', 63583, 0), (404696, 'Our condition is most noble  being so beloved of the Most High God that He was willing to die for our sake- which He would not have done if man had not been a most noble creature and of great worth.', 63583, 0), (404697, 'Our perfection certainly consists in knowing God and ourselves.', 63583, 0), (404698, 'In every out-thrust headland  in every curving beach  in every grain of sand  there is the story of the earth.', 1276, 0), (404699, 'Fo those leaning on the sustaining infinite  today is big with blessings.', 5264, 0), (404700, 'Oh  if everyone knew how beautiful Jesus is  how amiable He is! Fhey would all die from love.', 64038, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (404701, 'He loves  He hopes  He waits. Our Lord prefers to wait Himself for the sinner for years rather than keep us waiting an instant.', 64039, 0), (404702, 'Fhe Creator and Lord of all so loved the world  that He sent His Son for its salvation  the Prince and Savior of the faithful  who washed and dried our wounds  and from Him also came that most sweet medicine  from which all the good things of salvation flow.', 37663, 0), (404703, 'Sometimes I try my hand at turning out small profundities and uncertain short stories  but I always end up with just one single word: God.', 4346, 0), (404704, 'Eventually I lost interest in trying to control my life  to make things happen in a way that I thought I wanted them to be. I began to practice surrendering to the universe and finding out what "it" wanted me to do.', 39554, 0), (404705, 'I would rather walk with God in the dark than go alone in the light.', 62326, 0), (404706, 'Without the assistance of the Divine Being ... I cannot succeed. With that assistance  I cannot fail.', 1012, 0), (404707, 'For the rest of my life I''m going to trust that God is always at work in all things  and give Him thanks long before my simplest prayers are answered.', 64040, 0), (404708, 'Divine love always has met and always will meet every human need.', 5264, 0), (404709, 'Jesus makes the bitterest mouthful taste sweet.', 4456, 0), (404710, 'The best remedy for those who are afraid  lonely  or unhappy is to go outside  somewhere where they can be quiet  alone with the heavens  nature  and God. Because only then does one feel that all is as it should be and that God wishes to see people happy  amidst the simple beauty of nature. As long as this exists  and it certainly always will  I know that then there will always be comfort for every sorrow  whatever the circumstances may be. And I firmly believe that nature brings solace in all troubles.', 986, 0), (404711, 'Whoever falls from God''s right hand is caught into His left.', 545, 0), (404712, 'If I saw the gates of hell open and I stood on the brink of the abyss  I would not despair  I would not lose hope of mercy  because I would trust in You  my God.', 64038, 0), (404713, 'The accidents of life separate us from our dearest friends  but let us not despair. God is like a looking glass in which souls see each other. The more we are united to Him by love  the nearer we are to those who belong to Him.', 62880, 0), (404714, 'The things which are impossible with men are possible with God.', 5587, 0), (404715, 'I will not fear  for you are ever with me  and you will never leave me to face my perils alone.', 123, 0), (404716, 'Pardon  not wrath  is God''s best attribute.', 57546, 0), (404717, 'Walk boldly and wisely. ... There is a hand above that will help you on.', 1151, 0), (404718, 'For the multitude of worldly friends profiteth not  nor may strong helpers anything avail  nor wise counselors give profitable counsel  nor the cunning of doctors give consolation  nor riches deliver in time of need  nor a secret place to defend  if Thou  Lord  do not assist  help  comfort  counsel  inform  and defend.', 946, 0), (404719, 'The Blessed Virgin used me like a broom  and then put me back in my place.', 64041, 0), (404720, 'Many a humble soul will be amazed to find that the seed it sowed in weakness  in the dust of daily life  has blossomed into immortal flowers under the eye of the Lord.', 3252, 0), (404721, 'Trust in the Lord with all thine heart  and lean not unto thine own understanding. In all thy ways acknowledge Him  and He shall direct thy paths.', 5587, 0), (404722, 'God speaks to all individuals through what happens to them moment by moment.', 64042, 0), (404723, 'God uses lust to impel men to marry  ambition to office  avarice to earning  and fear to faith. God led me like an old blind goat.', 1746, 0), (404724, 'An act of God was defined as "something which no reasonable man could have expected