INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (404951, 'The art of governing consists in not letting men grow old in their jobs.', 1702, 0), (404952, 'The worst thing in this world  next to anarchy  is government.', 2175, 0), (404953, 'The legitimate object of government is to do for a community of people  whatever they need to have done  but cannot do at all  or cannot so well do for themselves  in their separate and individual capacities.', 1012, 0), (404954, 'That government is best which governs the least  because its people discipline themselves.', 1207, 0), (404955, 'How can you govern a country with two hundred and forty-six varieties of cheese?', 11599, 0), (404956, 'There is but one way for a president to deal with the Congress  and that is continuously  incessantly  and without interruption. If it''s really going to work  the relationship between the president and the Congress has got to be almost incestuous.', 1763, 0), (404957, 'The illegal we do immediately. The unconstitutional takes a little longer.', 2393, 0), (404958, 'The average man that I encounter all over the country regards government as a sort of great milk cow  with its head in the clouds eating air  and growing a full teat for everybody on earth.', 64089, 0), (404959, 'To make certain that crime does not pay  the government should take it over and try to run it.', 64090, 0), (404960, 'The strongest pressure in the world can be friendly pressure.', 62769, 0), (404961, 'The art of putting the right men in the right places is first in the science of government  but that of finding places for the discontented is the most difficult.', 62615, 0), (404962, 'It is common sense to take a method and try it. If it fails  admit it frankly and try another  but above all  try something.', 2261, 0), (404963, 'The government is becoming the family of last resort.', 63172, 0), (404964, 'All this will not be finished in the first one hundred days. Nor will it be finished in the first one thousand days  nor in the life of this administration  nor even perhaps in our lifetime on this planet.', 1680, 0), (404965, 'Governments last as long as the undertaxed can defend themselves against the overtaxed.', 8122, 0), (404966, 'The impersonal hand of government can never replace the helping hand of a neighbour.', 64091, 0), (404967, 'Too bad that all the people who know how to run the country are busy driving taxicabs and cutting hair.', 1643, 0), (404968, 'When we got into office  the thing that surprised me most was to find that things were just as bad as we''d been saying they were.', 1680, 0), (404969, 'No government can be long secure without a formidable opposition.', 1827, 0), (404970, 'The dogmas of the quiet past are inadequate to the stormy present. The occasion is piled high with difficulty and we must rise with the occasion. As our case is new  so we must think anew and act anew. We must disenthrall ourselves  and then we shall save our country.', 1012, 0), (404971, 'When I am abroad  I always make it a rule never to criticize or attack the government of my own country. I make up for lost time when I come home.', 3621, 0), (404972, 'The people''s right to change what does not work is one of the greatest principles of our system of government.', 20900, 0), (404973, 'No intelligence system can predict what a government will do if it doesn''t know itself.', 62407, 0), (404974, 'The U.S. Senate - an old scow which doesn''t move very fast  but never sinks.', 32578, 0), (404975, 'The supply of government exceeds the demand.', 13998, 0), (404976, 'Tyranny is yielding to the lust of governing.', 64092, 0), (404977, 'The safety of the State is the highest law.', 64093, 0), (404978, 'Experience teaches us to be most on our guard to protect liberty when the government''s purposes are beneficient.', 64094, 0), (404979, 'Government is a contrivance of human wisdom to provide for human wants.', 2026, 0), (404980, 'Government is a trust  and the officers of the government are trustees  and both the trust and the trustees are created for the benefit of the people.', 46469, 0), (404981, 'Though the people support the government the government should not support the people.', 18162, 0), (404982, 'I think we have more machinery of government than is necessary  too many parasites living on the labor of the industrious.', 1207, 0), (404983, 'The will of the people is the only legitimate foundation of any government  and to protect its free expression should be our first object.', 1207, 0), (404984, 'Govern a great nation as you would cook a small fish. (Don''t overdo it.)', 63016, 0), (404985, 'No man is good enough to govern another man without that other''s consent.', 1012, 0), (404986, 'A house divided against itself cannot stand - I believe this government cannot endure permanently half-slave and half-free.', 1012, 0), (404987, 'Every nation has the government that it deserves.', 2790, 0), (404988, 'Democracy is direct self-government  over all the people  for all the people  by all the people.', 1771, 0), (404989, 'Governments exist to protect the rights of minorities. The loved and the rich need no protection  - they have many friends and few enemies.', 24952, 0), (404990, 'No man undertakes a trade he has not learned  even the meanest  yet every one thinks himself sufficiently qualified for the hardest of all trades - that of government.', 1595, 0), (404991, 'It seems to me that government is like a pump  and what it pumps up is just what we are  a fair sample of the intellect  the ethics and the morals of the people  no better  no worse.', 28686, 0), (404992, 'Themistocles said  "The Athenians govern the Greeks  I govern the Athenians  you  my wife  govern me  your son governs you."', 4891, 0), (404993, 'The basis of our political systems is the right of the people to make and to alter their constitutions of government.', 3161, 0), (404994, 'An outward and visible sign of an inward and spiritual grace.', 33, 0), (404995, 'There