INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (405801, 'Our Thoughts Determine Our Happiness High above hate I dwell  0 storms! Farewell.', 64188, 0), (405802, 'The happiness of your life depends upon the quality of your thoughts.', 267, 0), (405803, '1 am happy and content because I think I am.', 64120, 0), (405804, 'All happiness is in the mind.', 33, 0), (405805, 'Happiness is not a matter of events  it depends upon the tides of the mind.', 62853, 0), (405806, 'A happy life consists in tranquility of mind.', 20928, 0), (405807, 'The real winners in life are the people who look at every situation with an expectation that they can make it work or make it better.', 64189, 0), (405808, 'A man''s as miserable as he thinks he is.', 62237, 0), (405809, 'The happiest person is the person who thinks the most interesting thoughts.', 6067, 0), (405810, 'Unhappiness indicates wrong thinking  just as ill health indicates a bad regimen.', 31300, 0), (405811, 'He is happy that knoweth not himself to be otherwise.', 1348, 0), (405812, 'The greater part of our happiness or misery depends on our dispositions  and not our circumstances.', 1953, 0), (405813, 'Happiness does not depend on outward things  but on the way we see them.', 93, 0), (405814, 'Happiness will never be any greater than the idea we have of it.', 2006, 0), (405815, 'We are never so happy or so unhappy as we think.', 154, 0), (405816, 'Misery is almost always the result of thinking.', 8895, 0), (405817, 'A great obstacle to happiness is to expect too much happiness.', 64190, 0), (405818, 'It isn''t our position  but our disposition  that makes us happy.', 33, 0), (405819, 'A man''s happiness or unhappiness depends as much on his temperament as on his destiny.', 154, 0), (405820, 'I went back to being an amateur  in the sense of somebody who loves what she is doing. If a professional loses the love of work  routine sets in  and that''s the death of work and life.', 64154, 0), (405821, 'The high prize of life  the crowning fortune of man  is to be born with a bias to some pursuit which finds him in employment and happiness.', 760, 0), (405822, 'The medals don''t mean anything and the glory doesn''t last. It''s all about your happiness. The rewards are going to come  but my happiness is just loving the sport and having fun performing.', 63993, 0), (405823, 'The road to happiness lies in two simple principles: find what it is that interests you and that you can do well  and when you find it put your whole soul into it-every bit of energy and ambition and natural ability you have.', 64191, 0), (405824, 'They are happy men whose natures sort with their vocations.', 1035, 0), (405825, 'Happiness consists in the full employment of our faculties in some pursuit.', 34936, 0), (405826, 'The happy people are those who are producing something.', 4228, 0), (405827, 'Congenial labor is the secret of happiness.', 62857, 0), (405828, 'To find out what one is fitted to do  and to secure an opportunity to do it  is the key to happiness.', 2575, 0), (405829, 'If I were to suggest a general rule for happiness  I would say "Work a little harder  Work a little longer  Work!"', 64192, 0), (405830, 'To make a man happy  fill his hands with work.', 64140, 0), (405831, 'Work is the true elixir of life. The busiest man is the happiest man.', 64165, 0), (405832, 'Happiness ... loves to see men work. She loves sweat  weariness  self-sacrifice. She will not be found in the palaces  but lurking in cornfields and factories  and hovering over littered desks.', 10420, 0), (405833, 'Every job has drudgery. ... The first secret of happiness is the recognition of this fundamental fact.', 62241, 0), (405834, 'All happiness depends on courage and work.', 143, 0), (405835, 'There is work that is work and there is play that is play  there is play that is work and work that is play. And in only one of these lie happiness.', 63129, 0), (405836, 'Employment... is so essential to human happiness that indolence is justly considered the mother of misery.', 6261, 0), (405837, 'Happiness comes only when we push our brains and hearts to the farthest reaches of which we are capable.', 40271, 0), (405838, 'A man is relieved and gay when he has put his heart into his work and done his best.', 760, 0), (405839, 'There is certainly no greater happiness than to be able to look back on a life usefully and virtuously employed  to trace our own progress in existence by such tokens as excite neither shame nor sorrow.', 2087, 0), (405840, 'Continuity of purpose is one of the most essential ingredients of happiness in the long run  and for most men this comes chiefly through their work.', 95, 0), (405841, 'Blessed is he who has found his work  let him ask no other blessedness. He has a work  a life-purpose. ... Get your happiness out of your work or you will never know what real happiness is. ... Even in the meanest sorts of labor  the whole soul of a man is composed into a kind of real harmony the instant he sets himself to work.', 3061, 0), (405842, 'Man is happy only as he finds a work worth doing-and does it well.', 64193, 0), (405843, 'Life without absorbing occupation is hell.', 4, 0), (405844, 'Few persons realize how much of their happiness  such as it is  is dependent upon their work.', 1069, 0), (405845, 'Joy is the will which labours  which overcomes obstacles  which knows triumph.', 62867, 0), (405846, 'Get happiness out of your work or you may never know what happiness is.', 4, 0), (405847, 'When men are rightly occupied  their amusement grows out of their work  as the color-petals out of a fruitful flower.', 485, 0), (405848, 'Parents  however old they and we may grow to be  serve among other things to shield us from a sense of our doom. As long as they are around  we can avoid the fact of our mortality  we can still be innocent children.', 63158, 0), (405849, 'You leave home to seek your fortune and  when you get it  you go home and share it with your family.', 12437, 0), (405850, 'Sometimes the strength of motherhood is greater than natural laws.', 679, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (405851, 'He is happiest  be he king or peasant  who finds peace in his home.', 62224, 0), (405852, 'My child looked at me and I looked back at him in the delivery room  and I realized that out of a sea of infinite possibilities it had come down to this: a specific person  born on the hottest day of the year  conceived on a Christmas Eve  made by his father and me miraculously from scratch.', 1552, 0), (405853, 'And when our baby stirs and struggles to be born it compels humility: what we began is now its own.', 64194, 0), (405854, 'What families have in common the world around is that they are the place where people learn who they are and how to be that way.', 64195, 0), (405855, 'Family life is the source of the greatest human happiness.', 63869, 0), (405856, 'Where thou art  that is home.', 91, 0), (405857, 'Parenting  at its best  comes as naturally as laughter. It is automatic  involuntary  unconditional love.', 64196, 0), (405858, 'If this world affords true happiness  it is to be found in a home where love and confidence increase with the years  where the necessities of life come without severe strain  where luxuries enter only after their cost has been carefully considered.', 6168, 0), (405859, 'There are four things a child needs: plenty of love  nourishing food  regular sleep  and lots of soap and water.', 51389, 0), (405860, 'Family jokes  though rightly cursed by strangers  are the bond that keeps most families alive.', 64197, 0), (405861, 'The secret of a happy marriage is finding the right person. You know they''re right if you love to be with them all of the time.', 1537, 0), (405862, 'An easygoing husband is the one indispensable comfort of life.', 4093, 0), (405863, 'My father got me strong and straight and slim And I give thanks to him. My mother bore me glad and sound and sweet  I kiss her feet.', 64198, 0), (405864, 'A house is not a home unless it contains food and fire for the mind as well as the body.', 2792, 0), (405865, 'No music is so pleasant to my ears as that word-father.', 59119, 0), (405866, 'He who leaves his house in search of happiness pursues a shadow.', 33, 0), (405867, 'If solid happiness we prize  within our breast this jewel lies  And they are fools who roam  the world has nothing to bestow  From our own selves our bliss must flow  And that dear hut-our home.', 62303, 0), (405868, 'Happiness grows at our own firesides  and is not to be picked in strangers'' gardens.', 62449, 0), (405869, 'A mother''s arms are more comforting than anyone else''s.', 2068, 0), (405870, 'He who would be happy should stay at home.', 32355, 0), (405871, 'Every family is a "normal" family- no matter whether it has one parent  two  or no children at all.', 63867, 0), (405872, 'Within our family there was no such thing as a person who did not matter. Second cousins thrice removed mattered.', 10890, 0), (405873, 'All the wealth of the world cannot be compared with the happiness of living together happily united.', 64199, 0), (405874, 'There''s a thread that binds all of us together  pull one end of the thread  the strain is felt all down the line.', 64200, 0), (405875, 'Love from one being to another can only be that two solitudes come nearer  recognize and protect and comfort each other.', 48566, 0), (405876, 'Happiness is good health and a bad memory.', 336, 0), (405877, 'Where there is laughter there is always more health than sickness.', 58461, 0), (405878, 'In the Orient people believed that the basis of all disease was unhappiness. Thus to make a patient happy again was to restore him to health.', 64201, 0), (405879, 'Loving  like prayer  is a power as well as a process. It''s curative. It is creative.', 64202, 0), (405880, 'The simple truth is that happy people generally don''t get sick.', 39552, 0), (405881, 'Laughter is by definition healthy.', 217, 0), (405882, 'Laughter is the best medicine.', 33, 0), (405883, 'Love is the great miracle cure. Loving ourselves works miracles in our lives.', 5296, 0), (405884, 'Happiness is not being pained in body nor troubled in mind.', 1207, 0), (405885, 'One of the quickest ways to become exhausted is by suppressing your feelings.', 47532, 0), (405886, 'Being asked one day what was the surest way of remaining happy in this world  the Emperor Sigismund of Germany replied: "Only do in health what you have promised to do when you were sick."', 33, 0), (405887, 'The best things in life aren''t things.', 3199, 0), (405888, 'Money  or even power  can never yield happiness unless it be accompanied by the goodwill of others.', 14130, 0), (405889, 'To fulfill a dream  to be allowed to sweat over lonely labor  to be given the chance to create  is the meat and potatoes of life. The money is the gravy.', 13058, 0), (405890, 'I don''t want to make money. I just want to be wonderful.', 1, 0), (405891, 'It''s pretty hard to tell what does bring happiness  poverty and wealth have both failed.', 14120, 0), (405892, 'It is neither wealth nor splendor  but tranquility and occupation  which give happiness.', 1207, 0), (405893, 'Joy has nothing to do with material things  or with a man''s outward circumstance ... a man living in the lap of luxury can be wretched  and a man in the depths of poverty can overflow with joy.', 18978, 0), (405894, 'Hope costs nothing.', 244, 0), (405895, 'Getting what you go after is success  but liking it while you are getting it is happiness.', 64203, 0), (405896, 'Success can also cause misery. The trick is not to be surprised when you discover it doesn''t bring you all the happiness and answers you thought it would.', 12819, 0), (405897, 'No social system will bring us happiness  health and prosperity unless it is inspired by something greater than materialism.', 64204, 0), (405898, 'The essence of philosophy is that a man should so live that his happiness shall depend as little as possible on external things.', 1328, 0), (405899, 'Happiness depends  as Nature shows  less on exterior things than most suppose.', 8676, 0), (405900, 'There are two things to aim at in life: first  to get what you want  and  after that  to enjoy it. Only the wisest of mankind achieve the second.', 1014, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (405901, 'In this world there are only two tragedies. One is not getting what one wants  and the other is getting it.', 40, 0), (405902, 'A life of frustration is inevitable for any coach whose main enjoyment is winning.', 62232, 0), (405903, 'Money is human happiness in the abstract  he  then  who is no longer capable of enjoying human happiness in the concrete devotes himself utterly to money.', 1304, 0), (405904, 'Happiness seems to require a modicum of external prosperity.', 1116, 0), (405905, 'Those who have easy  cheerful attitudes tend to be happier than those with less pleasant temperaments regardless of money  "making it" or success.', 62254, 0), (405906, 'Money  or even power  can never yield happiness unless it be accompanied by the goodwill of others.', 14130, 0), (405907, 'The secret of happiness is to admire without desiring.', 64205, 0), (405908, 'Few rich men own their own property. Their property owns them.', 1980, 0), (405909, 'We can be wise from goodness and good from wisdom.', 20540, 0), (405910, 'She knew what all smart women knew: Laughter made you live better and longer.', 64206, 0), (405911, 'An Arabian proverb says there are four sorts of men: He who knows not and knows not he knows not: he is a fool-shun him. He who knows not and knows he knows not: he is simple-teach him. He who knows and knows not he knows: he is asleep-wake him. He who knows and knows he knows: he is wise-follow him.', 64207, 0), (405912, 'There are only two things that are absolute realities  love and knowledge  and you can''t escape them.', 25143, 0), (405913, 'Wisdom is the most important part of happiness.', 139, 0), (405914, 'Knowledge is the prime need of the hour.', 25698, 0), (405915, 'Better be happy than wise.', 33, 0), (405916, 'Be happy. It''s one way of being wise.', 244, 0), (405917, 'With happiness comes intelligence to the heart.', 7652, 0), (405918, 'Joy is the holy fire that keeps our purpose warm and our intelligence aglow.', 701, 0), (405919, 'Our happiness depends on wisdom all the way.', 139, 0), (405920, 'The genius of happiness is still so rare  is indeed on the whole the rarest genius. To possess it means to approach life with the humility of a beggar  but to treat it with the proud generosity of a prince  to bring to its totality the deep understanding of a great poet and to each of its moments the abandonment and ingenuousness of a child.', 62381, 0), (405921, 'What matters most is that we learn from living.', 217, 0), (405922, 'Best trust the happy moments. ... The days that make us happy make us wise.', 15461, 0), (405923, 'It is an aspect of all happiness to suppose that we deserve it.', 8895, 0), (405924, 'A garden isn''t meant to be useful. It''s for joy.', 14002, 0), (405925, 'A reasonable man needs only to practice moderation to find happiness.', 62224, 0), (405926, 'To forget oneself is to be happy.', 449, 0), (405927, 'Happiness is a resultant of the relative strengths of positive and negative feelings rather than an absolute amount of one or the other.', 64121, 0), (405928, 'The first recipe for happiness is: Avoid too lengthy meditations on the past.', 10019, 0), (405929, 'Man needs  for his happiness  not only the enjoyment of this or that  but hope and enterprise and change.', 95, 0), (405930, 'Happy is the man who can do only one thing  in doing it  he fulfills his destiny.', 8895, 0), (405931, 'And may I live the remainder of my life ... for myself  may there be plenty of books and many years'' store of the fruits of the earth!', 2542, 0), (405932, 'Behold  we count them happy which endure.', 5587, 0), (405933, 'The will of man is his happiness.', 62240, 0), (405934, 'Happiness to a dog is what lies on the other side of the door.', 62223, 0), (405935, 'The supreme happiness of life is the conviction that we are loved.', 98, 0), (405936, 'The happiness of a man in this life does not consist in the absence  but in the mastery  of his 